equality but each generation has a new chance to believe and make it so.

All of you complaining about not understanding why the song doesn't include 
all colors of people really need to watch the episode that the song is in 
before you criticize it. The song is in the Proud to be Me episode. Segi is 
the president of the Sesame Street Snazzy Society. Abby, Elmo, Big Bird and 
Segi do a dance then she reads a book to the club. She stops reading when 
the character in the book rejects a toy because of it's color which just so 
happens to be the color of Segi's skin. She thinks that being brown is 
uncool because of the character in the book that she admires. Snazzy Jazzy 
can't possibly be wrong...or can she? And that is what the song sets out to 
teach Segi. There is another song in the episode about skin which 
encompasses all shades and colors. This one just so happens to be for 
children who are brown who need to know that they are special, unique, good 
enough, AND snazzy.﻿
